abstract: The Dow, which closed up 124.17 points at 9,789.36 on Monday, is within reach of 10,000. Who would have thought?
snippet: The Dow, which closed up 124.17 points at 9,789.36 on Monday, is within reach of 10,000. Who would have thought?
lead_paragraph: It is only a number — the stock market equivalent of an appliance chain’s millionth customer, or the gazillionth hamburger served at McDonald’s.

headline.main: Creeping Up to 5 Digits Yet Again
